  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "When `p2p-peer-upper-bound` > `p2p-peer-lower-bound` (default value: 64) without explicitly setting the lower bound option, the lower bound is set to the upper bound value but on the `DiscoveryConfig` builder only. Then the upper bound is compared to the default lower bound (64) and hence set to 64. We end up with p2p-peer-upper-bound == p2p-peer-lower-bound == 64\r\n\r\nCheck:\r\n```\r\nd.isDiscoveryEnabled(p2pDiscoveryEnabled)\r\n                  .staticPeers(p2pStaticPeers)\r\n                  .minPeers(getP2pLowerBound())\r\n                  .maxPeers(getP2pUpperBound())\r\n                  .siteLocalAddressesEnabled(siteLocalAddressesEnabled);\r\n```\r\nin `P2POptions`\r\n\r\n[Reported on Discord](https://discord.com/channels/697535391594446898/697539289042649190/1100124015529578660)\r\n",
